Date: Tue, 26 Aug 2003 07:16:44 -0400
From: Dr. Michael Parry <MParry@stamhealth.org


Please note, your editorial on this item should say "...by virtue of O157's
INABILITY to ferment sorbitol..."

--
Michael Parry
Director of Infectious Diseases
Stamford Hospital, CT, USA.
<MParry@stamhealth.org


[ProMED and this moderator acknowledge Dr. Parry's correction of post
20030825.2144. Indeed, it is the inability of _E. coli_ O157:H7 to ferment
sorbitol that distinguishes its growth on sorbitol-MacConkey agar. - Mod. LL]
